summary: human papillomaviruses (HPVs) are highly diverse and have been classified into five genera. a subset of HPVs cause anogenital or head and neck cancers (2–4), while others cause noncancerous skin growths. the L1 gene of HPV-Fin864 showed a best BLASTn match to HPV-156. the papillomavirus genus currently consists of 10 viral species known to infect humans.
